│ - `freeze(zext(x))` is not equivalent to `sext(freeze(x))`.                                                                  │
│ - With input `x = true (1)`, `zext(x)` is `1`. `freeze(1)` is `1`.                                                           │
│ - With input `x = true (1)`, `freeze(x)` is `true (1)`. `sext(true)` is `-1`.                                                │
│ This difference in value (`1` vs `-1`) causes the `icmp ugt` to produce a different result, leading to the miscompilation.   │
│                                                                                                                              │
